<div class="content" name="BackupCloseFile" uuid="f9137a7a-f47e-41c9-a4ae-61f1757e908b"><p>The BackupCloseFile method closes the database file that was
initialized by a prior call to the <span><a href="f5fc08ea-2f9f-438d-93d2-4f8e6813df46" data-linktype="relative-path">BackupOpenFile</a></span>.</p><dl>
<dd>
<div><pre> HRESULT BackupCloseFile();
</pre></div>
</dd></dl><p>This method has no parameters.</p><p>If Config_CA_Interface_Flags contains the value
IF_NOREMOTEICERTADMINBACKUP, the server SHOULD return an error.<a id="Appendix_A_Target_68"></a><a aria-label="Product behavior note 68" href="5f06c74c-1a29-4fdf-b8dd-ae3300d1b90d#Appendix_A_68" data-linktype="relative-path">&lt;68&gt;</a></p><p>The <span><a href="c6451297-197d-4b4b-b786-3f3187b67b8f#gt_c925d5d7-a442-4ba4-9586-5f94ccec847a" data-linktype="relative-path">CA</a></span> server MUST
enforce the sequencing rules for the BackupCloseFile, as specified in section <span><a href="e37640b4-b2e1-4bac-89d2-61fc5a5e6c1d" data-linktype="relative-path">3.1.4.1.18</a></span>.</p></div>